Thus, under the following conditions, the votes contained in one or more election packages may be partially counted The results of the protocols do not agree; the Protocol on Voting and Calculation is not actually available or it is not owned by the Chairman of the Election Committee or there are obvious errors or amendments to the minutes.
In addition, the total counting of the fully filled voting certificates may be carried out if there is a difference between the contested winner and the one standing in the second place that is equal or less than one percentage, provided that at the beginning of the meeting there is an explicit request from the party-to-coalition chairman who is the second of those candidates.
The vote counting may also take place in its entirety if, after the conclusion of the ordinary calculation, the difference between the contested winner and the candidate at the second place is equal or less than a percentage, provided that an explicit request is made by a representative of the party whose candidate has become the second. In this case, the election packages which have been exposed to a partial explanation would be excluded.
